<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Cap_and_Floor"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Cap_and_Floor"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange Cap and Floor trades.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Cap and Floor Trades</title>

    <para role="TEXT">Cap and Floor trades are a combination of an interest rate cap and
    an interest rate floor. A cap is a financial contract giving the owner the
    right, but not the obligation, to borrow a pre-set amount of money at a
    pre-set interest rate with a pre-set maturity date. A floor is a financial
    contract giving the owner the right, but not the obligation, to lend a
    pre-set amount of money at a pre-set interest rate with a pre-set maturity
    date.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Caps and floors refer to interest rate agreements in which payments
    are made. For caps, the payments are made when the reference rate exceeds
    the strike rate. For floors, the payments are made when the reference rate
    falls below the strike rate.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Many procedures for swaps are also applicable to caps and floors.
    Procedures on date and schedule generation, interest calculation, stubs,
    amortization, and averaging and compounding deals apply to many
    derivatives. Here, we concentrate on features specific to caps and
    floors.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">If the cap or floor is in a non-base currency trade, the appropriate
    FX Rates also are needed to translate it back into base currency.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">The following guidelines apply to Cap/Floor trade entry:</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">Start with minimum input and have the system generate as much of
        your information as possible</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">Make sure the dates are generated correctly</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">Customize the trade (with respect to dates and rates) only as a
        last resort</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>

