              </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Counterparty</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Required. Name of a
              counterparty to be associated with the trade. Select from the
              dropdown list.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Portfolio</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Required. Name of the
              portfolio to be associated with the trade. Select from the
              dropdown list.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Effective
              Date</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Effective date of the trade.
              </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Termination
              Date</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Required. Termination date of
              the trade. </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Buy/Sell</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Select one of the option
              buttons:</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis role="bold">Buy</emphasis>
              indicates that you are to purchase the option, and therefore
              will pay the option premium.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
              role="bold">Sell</emphasis> indicates that you are to sell the
              option, and therefore will receive the option
              premium.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Cap/Floor</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Select one of the option
              buttons:</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis role="bold">Cap</emphasis> - for
              protection against rate increases. The payments are made when
              the reference rate exceeds the strike
              rate.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis role="bold">Floor</emphasis> – for
              protection against rate decreases. The payments are made when
              the reference rate falls below the strike rate.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guibutton>Pay
              Flows</guibutton></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Click this button to open the
              Pay Flows window.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guibutton>Pay
              Schedule</guibutton></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Click this button to open the
              Pay Schedule window.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Notional
              Amount</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Notional amount of the trade.
              In the first field, specify the currency - click the magnifying
              glass icon to select. In the second field, specify the notional
              amount of the trade.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Strike</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">The <emphasis
              role="bold">Strike price</emphasis>, also known as the <emphasis
              role="bold">Exercise price</emphasis>, is the stated price per
              share for which the underlying stock may be purchased (in the
              case of a call) or sold (in the case of a put) by the Option
              holder upon exercising the Option contract.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Index</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Specifies the index to be
              used with the trade. Select from the dropdown
              list</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Term</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Index term for floating legs.
              The system recognizes alphanumeric combinations like 3M (for
              three months) 6M (six months), 1Y (one year), 3Y (three years),
              etc.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Basis</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Day count convention used to
              calculate the number of days in an interest payment period.
              Please see <emphasis>Table 1 - Day Count Convention</emphasis>
              in chapter <emphasis>Tables</emphasis> for more
              information.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Spread
              (BP)</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Enter the spread percentage
              in basis points of the trade.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1"
              rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Formula</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Field in which the selected
              formula appears. Click the <guibutton>Create Formula</guibutton>
              button to create a formula.</para></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

